OL,3,CFA to name and shame grassroots clubs
OL,4,Cwho fail to curb touchline abuse
OL,6,F"Sadly, a concerning proportion of
OL,7,Fthem can make specific references to
OL,8,Fpoor adult conduct in their game and
OL,9,Fwe need to firstly accept this, but
OL,10,Fsecondly take responsibility to put it
OL,11,Fright and challenge where appropriate.
OL,12,FFootball is a game for all, and must
OL,13,Fremain that way."
